\newlabel{fig:map_clim}{{4}{12}{Climatology of the AROME model (first row), Météo-France stations (second row), and the AROME--Station difference (third row), with the spatial correlation between the stations and their closest grid points ($r$), the bias ($ME$) and the number of stations compared (n). The statistics of the three first columns are derived from daily data from 1959 to 2022. The last columns uses hourly data from 1990 to 2022. The contour lines show the 400 and 800 m isolines. To ease visualization, colour scales are symmetrically saturated above the 99.9th percentile for the number of days and the 99th percentile for annual and 10-year return level precipitation)}{figure.caption.4}{}}
