\newlabel{fig:map_monthly_trend}{{8}{17}{Relative trends over the last thirty years ending in 2022 (\%) in the 10-year return level of hourly precipitation for AROME (left) and Météo-France stations (right), with the correlation ($r$), the number of stations compared (n), and the bias ($ME$). These results are derived by fitting, at each location, the selected GEV model to daily precipitation maxima from 1990 to 2022. The contour lines show the 400 and 800 m isolines. To ease visualization, colour scales are symmetrically saturated using a 90\% threshold. All maps are clipped to this common percentile range. Only statistically significant trends are shown, non-significant trends are set to zero}{figure.caption.8}{}}
